Package nl.utwente.jmlplugin.completion

Class JMLCompletionUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.utwente.jmlplugin.completion.JMLCompletionUtils
  • public class JMLCompletionUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    Various utility methods that are needed by the various completion providers. Most completion providers have their logic decoupled into this utility class as a lot of code needs to be shared across many providers.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      static class  JMLCompletionUtils.expressionLocation
      Enum for JML expression location, this is needed for context aware completion of JML keywords that can be mixed with Java.

      • sortResults

        public static void sortResults​(@NotNull
                               @NotNull com.intellij.codeInsight.completion.CompletionParameters params,
                               @NotNull
                               @NotNull com.intellij.codeInsight.completion.CompletionResultSet results)
        Reuse of IntelliJ's completion results sorting algorithm, doesn't work as well as normal as much of the completion that is made by IntelliJ is heavily dependent on context and a proper Java parse tree. But this works better than anything I can come up with, so we use this.
        Parameters:
        params - - completion context.
        results - - completion results holder.

        public static boolean fillMethodParameterDotCompletions​(@NotNull

                                                        @NotNull
                                                        @NotNull com.intellij.codeInsight.completion.CompletionResultSet results)
        Fill in completions for . expressions when they are called on a method parameter, only single dot expressions are supported as we do not have our own recursive type resolver.
        Parameters:
        params - - completion context.
        results - - completion results holder.
        Returns:
        true if the type of the method parameter could be resolved and completions filled in, false otherwise.

      • fillJMLKeywordCompletions

        public static boolean fillJMLKeywordCompletions​(@NotNull
                                                @NotNull com.intellij.codeInsight.completion.CompletionParameters params,
                                                @NotNull
                                                @NotNull com.intellij.codeInsight.completion.CompletionResultSet results)
        Hack method for providing singly chained . completions for JMLKeywords. To do this properly a recursive type resolver that accounts for JMLKeywords is necessary, so until one is made, this is the stopgap.
        Parameters:
        params - - completion context.
        results - - completion result holder.
        Returns:
        true if the type of the keyword could be resolved and the completions filled in, false otherwise.
